phrases: We will leave you behind, slowpoke!
I am with the Shinjuku Ward Office.
So you just brought him here?
That does not mean you can just...
He is saying that the stone statue where he lives was broken.
Some Anothers need a vessel to call home.
So his vessel was broken, and he lost his memories, huh?
Let us have a meeting, I guess?
All I can tell you is that it is part of a very old stone statue.
It is hard to say more with the equipment here.
I will scrape off a bit and have a guy I know at a university analyze it.
If only we knew his name.
Okay, I will go see if I can find clues
about what kind of Another he is, including his name.
Sakaki-kun, you have got to go help your sister, right?
She is finalizing her post-graduation plans...
I am behind on updating the database, too.
I am the one who brought him here.
Well, I guess it is all right.
Okay, I am leaving it to you.
Is there something you want to eat?
I will open it for you.
If he is the kind of Another that needs a vessel, there is a problem.
Without his vessel, he has no place to go.
Which means we have to give him a place to stay!
I will take him home for today, I guess.
What are you doing, bringing somebody who smells like a bear here?!
He is not even trying to hide his divine aura.
If he stays here, I will go crazy!
What do you think about your little sister's post-graduation plans?
Yes, well, for my part, I think my olderI mean, younger sister..
should do what makes her happy.
Do not spill it today, okay?
Let us go find you a place to live today.
We are not letting someone like that live with us for this!
Is it just me, or is that Another doing better?
Yeah, I have been walking around all day for days now,
and it is more exhausting than I thought.
Okay, I am off to keep looking for a place for him to go...
Let us search around the neighborhood today.
What kind of place would be good?
Who said you could come in here?
I am making this place my temporary home.
You look like a hunting god, which is probably why you are so reckless!
He just lost his vessel and memories, and is having a rough time.
Get him out of here, Seimei.
There will not be a next time.
Shrines already have gods in them.
It is hard to give that up.
You almost got into a fight, though.
If you find a vessel with no occupant, that would be one thing.
But failing that, a fight is inevitable.
If you try to go inside, there will be big trouble!
You should take better care of yourself.
Job or not, you are pushing yourself too hard.
Arata's life force is leaving his body and going somewhere.
Does that have something to do with him feeling better?
He looks surprised, which means he did not steal it deliberately.
Is he the type that drains you just by being nearby?
He is probably unconsciously taking energy from any human who focuses on him.
If I am sucking away your life force,
staying here any longer will mean killing you.
We have not found your name or a home for you!
I cannot take the life of an innocent man,
let alone one who is done so much for me.
My job is to find clues as to who you are!
We have been together this whole time.
Hey, I hate to interrupt your touching conversation,
but I have no idea what you are saying.
If we can find his name, we can find a new vessel for him.
Then we keep doing what we have been doing.
I will stay with that Another and find clues to his name.
And I may have lost my own stamina,
but that Another is doing better now.
Let us do what we can.
And we are the ones who gave him the job, after all.
Contact me AS SOON AS POSSIBLE if something happens.
I did not know there were so many people, and of so many different kinds.
Well, that is especially true for Shinjuku.
And I have never met a human like you before.
But it feels like something is coming back.
If you notice anything at all, tell me.
Then first, I request an offering.
I did not get any food after the fuss back there.
You must be hungry as well, right?
I will get something ready when we get home.
I just got some good honey there.
It is imported, and supposedly delicious.
A sparkle like dew on leaves changing color in fall...
A sweet scent that tickles the heart...
Men made an offering of this honey to me.
They would make offerings to me,
praying for peace for their cattle and children, and for fertile harvests...
This honey is from my homeland!
A god of the forests and the hunt,
worshiped in the Slavic myths that center around Ukraine.
He also protects cattle in the form of a bear.
That Another seemed to not want to kill you.
That narrowed it down a lot.
I guess we will not need this, then.
The Mental World of Ancient Ukraine
I thought it would be a clue.
But if you know who he is, then you do not need it now, huh?
What will happen to this statue after this?
It does not belong to this museum, so it will be sent back to its old museum,
or travel the world in the same way that it was brought here.
Places I do not know, that I have never been...
I have seen many things over these past few days.
If I can see more, then I am very lucky.
The gods need human emotions to survive.
Faith, fear, gratitude, wishes, and prayers.
But I was forgotten, and my power was lost.
Without you, I would have done nothing but wait for death.
But you turned your heart to me, and saved me.
A wonderful job, one you can be proud of.
I still never got your name.
I am Volos, God of the Rus!
I, my name, and my power
The bear guy finally left, huh?
It is because you tried to help a guy like that.
Hey, want to go have some fun?
I found some pretty cherry blossoms.
I am going back to the ward office.
I will be waiting at home, then!
Hey, if we cannot go see cherry blossoms, how about fishing?
I will go with you to work.
Most of the occult creatures you see in fiction.
We have a name for all these non-human creatures we use in our work.
and if they get into any problems with civilians, taking care of it.
That is the job of the Nocturnal Community Relations Division,
and our job at the Shinjuku Ward Office.
